line_1: Then said, in unsoot whispers, Fye! Sir, fye!
line_2: Nathless on me she cast a languid eye:

line_1: Then said, in unsoot whispers, Fye! Sir, fye!
line_2: Blist by thy form, my liefest life, quoth I,

line_1: Then said, in unsoot whispers, Fye! Sir, fye!
line_2: From love, alass! in vain my heart would fly;

line_1: Hearts then it is; spadille I lead, oh fie!
line_2: One hand without a trump! now hard they lie.
I wad na been surpriz'd to spy
You on an auld wife's flainen toy;
Or aiblins some bit duddie boy,
